---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '@/config/site';

const lastUpdated = '29 April 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms & Conditions of Sale"
  description={`Standard B2B terms and conditions of sale for ${site.legalName} — precast and prestressed concrete products.`}
  schema="Article"
>
  <section class="bg-navy text-white">
    <div class="container-wccp py-16 md:py-20">
      <p class="eyebrow text-yellow mb-4">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="font-display text-display-xl text-white mb-4">Terms &amp; Conditions of Sale</h1>
      <p class="text-white/90 text-lg max-w-2xl">
        These terms apply to all orders placed with {site.legalName}. They are written for business buyers under English law.
      </p>
      <p class="text-cast-200 text-sm mt-6">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-wccp py-16">
    <div class="max-w-prose-wide mx-auto space-y-8 text-cast-700 text-base leading-relaxed">

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">1. Definitions</h2>
        <p>
          "<strong class="text-navy">Seller</strong>" means {site.legalName}, company number {site.companyNumber},
          registered at {site.address.street}, {site.address.town}, {site.address.postcode}.
          "<strong class="text-navy">Buyer</strong>" means the business or organisation placing the order.
          "<strong class="text-navy">Goods</strong>" means the precast or prestressed concrete products to be supplied.
          "<strong class="text-navy">Contract</strong>" means the order accepted by the Seller subject to these terms.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">2. Application of these terms</h2>
        <p>
          These terms govern every Contract between Seller and Buyer to the exclusion of any other terms the Buyer
          seeks to impose, including any terms on the Buyer's purchase order. Variations are only binding if agreed
          in writing by a director of the Seller. These terms are supplied to business customers; nothing in them
          affects the statutory rights of consumers under the Consumer Rights Act 2015.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">3. Quotations and acceptance</h2>
        <p>
          Quotations are valid for 30 days from issue unless stated otherwise and may be withdrawn at any time before
          acceptance. An order is accepted only when the Seller issues a written acknowledgement or commences
          manufacture, whichever is sooner. The Seller reserves the right to decline any order.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">4. Specifications and drawings</h2>
        <p>
          Where the Buyer supplies drawings, specifications or measurements, the Buyer is responsible for their
          accuracy. The Seller may rely on them without independent verification. Standard catalogue dimensions are
          subject to manufacturing tolerances in line with BS EN 13369 and the relevant product standards.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">5. Prices and payment</h2>
        <p>
          Prices are exclusive of VAT and, unless stated, exclusive of delivery and offload. The Seller may revise
          prices for orders not despatched within 90 days of acceptance, on notice to the Buyer.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Payment terms for approved trade accounts are <strong class="text-navy">strictly 30 days from date of invoice</strong>.
          New customers without a credit account pay on a pro-forma basis before despatch. The Seller may suspend
          deliveries on any account in arrears. Late payment carries statutory interest at 8% above the Bank of
          England base rate under the Late Payment of Commercial Debts (Interest) Act 1998.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">6. Delivery</h2>
        <p>
          Delivery dates are estimates and not of the essence. The Seller will not be liable for delays caused by
          weather, transport disruption, or events outside its reasonable control. The Buyer is responsible for
          providing safe access for HGVs and (where applicable) HIAB offload, and for ensuring the site is ready to
          receive the Goods at the agreed time. Standing time may be charged where a vehicle is delayed beyond
          30 minutes through no fault of the Seller.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Risk passes to the Buyer on offload; title passes only when the Seller has received cleared payment in full
          for the Goods and any other sums owed (retention of title).
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">7. Inspection and returns</h2>
        <p>
          The Buyer must inspect the Goods on delivery and notify the Seller in writing of any shortage, damage or
          defect within 5 working days. Bespoke or made-to-order Goods are non-returnable. Catalogue Goods may be
          returned within 14 days subject to a restocking charge, where they are unused, undamaged and on original
          pallets.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">8. Warranty</h2>
        <p>
          The Seller warrants that Goods will, at the time of delivery, conform to the agreed specification and be
          free from defects in materials and workmanship. The Seller's sole liability under this warranty is, at its
          option, to replace defective Goods or refund the price. This warranty does not cover damage caused by
          incorrect installation, ground movement, chemical attack outside specified resistance, overloading, or
          ordinary wear and tear.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">9. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing in these terms limits or excludes liability for death or personal injury caused by negligence,
          fraud, fraudulent misrepresentation, or any other liability that cannot lawfully be limited.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Subject to that, the Seller's total liability under or in connection with the Contract — whether in contract,
          tort (including negligence), under statute or otherwise — is capped at the price paid for the Goods giving
          rise to the claim. The Seller is not liable for indirect or consequential losses, loss of profit, loss of
          revenue, loss of contracts, or loss of opportunity.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">10. Force majeure</h2>
        <p>
          Neither party is liable for any failure or delay caused by events outside their reasonable control,
          including but not limited to acts of God, war, terrorism, civil unrest, fire, flood, severe weather,
          pandemic, industrial action, or interruption of utilities, transport or raw-material supply.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">11. Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          All drawings, designs and technical literature supplied by the Seller remain the Seller's property and
          must not be copied, reused or shared with third parties without written consent.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">12. Data protection</h2>
        <p>
          Each party will comply with the UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018 in respect of any personal data
          shared under the Contract. See our <a href="/privacy" class="text-ember font-semibold hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a> for detail.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">13. Governing law and jurisdiction</h2>
        <p>
          The Contract is governed by the laws of England and Wales. Each party submits to the exclusive jurisdiction
          of the English courts.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-navy mb-3">14. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions on these terms: <a href={`mailto:${site.contact.email}`} class="text-ember font-semibold hover:underline">{site.contact.email}</a> ·
          <a href={`tel:${site.contact.phoneIntl}`} class="text-ember font-semibold hover:underline ml-1">{site.contact.phone}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
